HEADWORD: Macaca
<hw>Macaca</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>A genus of macaques including
the rhesus monkey (<spn>Macaca mulatta</spn>), much used in laboratory
biomedical research. Formerly called
<altname>Macacus</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> genus <gen>Macaca</gen>.</syn>⟦br⟧
